title: Delta pilots say they're willing to strike
description: Delta Air Lines pilots intensified their push for improved pay by insisting they will strike if they do not get a new contract.

title: Lee Ji Han, K-pop singer, killed in Seoul crowd crush
description: Lee Ji Han, a Korean actor and K-pop singer, was among the more than 150 victims who died during a crowd surge at a Halloween celebration in Seoul over the weekend, his management announced.

title: Bolsonaro remains silent after Brazil presidential election loss
description: More than 12 hours after Luiz Inacio Lula da Silva was pronounced the winner of Brazil's 2022 presidential election, incumbent Jair Bolsonaro has yet to publicly acknowledge his loss.

title: Richard Branson says he won't take part in Singapore televised death penalty debate
description: British entrepreneur Richard Branson has declined an invitation from the Singaporean government to take part in a live television debate on the death penalty.

title: Warnings grow of dire conditions at migrant processing center in England
description: British charities and officials are warning of increasingly dire conditions at a migrant processing center in England and urging Prime Minister Rishi Sunak to act.

title: Stellantis' joint venture in China is filing for bankruptcy
description: Stellantis said that shareholders of its loss-making joint venture producing Jeep vehicles in China have approved it to file for bankruptcy.
